# TypeScript Conventions

Strict mode is enabled. Follow these rules in all `.ts` files and `<script setup>` blocks.

## Types
```ts
// ✅ interface for object shapes
interface Exam { id: string; name: string; archived: boolean }

// ✅ type for unions, intersections, mapped types
type QuestionType = 'multiple-choice' | 'open-ended' | 'fill-in-the-blank' | 'ordering' | 'matching' | 'informational'
type PartialExam = Partial<Exam>

// ❌ never use any
const data: any = ...

// ❌ no unchecked casts — add a comment if unavoidable
const el = ref as HTMLInputElement  // must have justification comment
```

## Null Safety
```ts
// ✅ optional chaining and nullish coalescing
const name = exam?.version?.name ?? 'Untitled'

// ❌ non-null assertions without comment
const name = exam!.name
```

## Async / Error Handling
```ts
// ✅ always handle errors explicitly
try {
  await submitAttempt(id)
} catch (err) {
  console.error('Failed to submit attempt', err)
  notify.error(t('attempt.submitError'))
}

// ❌ silent catch
try { ... } catch {}
```

## Pinia Stores
```ts
// ✅ setup syntax
export const useExamStore = defineStore('exam', () => {
  const exams = ref<Exam[]>([])
  async function fetchExams() { ... }
  return { exams, fetchExams }
})
```

## Imports
- Use path aliases where configured (`src/` mapped as needed via Vite)
- Import Quasar config utilities from `#q-app/wrappers`
